reviews.text: Danielle was our courteous server and made sure our visit went well.  The facility is clean and has both indoor and outdoor seating.  We had the Italian sausage and flounder entrees and both were plentiful portions and came with hefty sides. The sausage was spicy and the Caesar salad was a meal of its own.  Only one bathroom exists for both genders so you may have a wait. Figure $30 per person.

Want to thank everyone at Paolo's for everything they did to make our event a success. The food was delicious and the servers kept replenishing the food even though we went well over the amount of people I originally quoted. As well the two bartenders were very friendly and very attentive. Good time all the way around. Great place to have a venue. Everyone had a lovely time. Great place for a party.

We were greeted immediately with a friendly smiling face. Seated at the table of our choice from what was free, and offered drinks up front. Our waitress was friendly and easy going. Our food was hot and fresh. I had stuffed shells which came in a metal dish on a plate. The dish had obviously been in the oven to melt the cheese and I was warned it would be hot. I even enjoyed a nice slice of Reece's peanut butter cake. I would highly recommend this for a night out with family or friends.
Great pizza. Really good crust and sauce. Reminds me of New York style pizza. And I got to take my tour de pizza cutter for a spin.

We have been eating in and taking out food at Paolo for many, many years but the sandwich I got today was the worst I ever had.  I ordered an Italian Sandwich.  The roll tasted stale.  The sandwich was very, very dry to the point of being hard to swallow.  Tasted and looked like it had very little oil.  I had to add some of my own.  You had to actually hunt for the lettuce and onions.  No taste at all.  It was very bland.  The last time I got one the experience was very similar.  I suggest unless you order pizza to find another place for your sandwich.

detailedReviews.author: Rosemary Smorey
detailedReviews.text: We have been eating in and taking out food at Paolo for many, many years but the sandwich I got today was the worst I ever had.  I ordered an Italian Sandwich.  The roll tasted stale.  The sandwich was very, very dry to the point of being hard to swallow.  Tasted and looked like it had very little oil.  I had to add some of my own.  You had to actually hunt for the lettuce and onions.  No taste at all.  It was very bland.  The last time I got one the experience was very similar.  I suggest unless you order pizza to find another place for your sandwich.

detailedReviews.author: Verna Hoover
detailedReviews.text: Stopped here for dinner, had not been in this place for probably 15 yrs or more. We ordered wings and a cheese steak and fries. When we got our food we could see that the wings looked very very well done, took a bite and they were hard and very dry and chewy, not good at all, we could not eat them. Next up was the cheese steak, 1st thing I noticed was didn't look like there was any cheese on this cheese steak, I put my readers on to have a closer look searching for any traces of cheese, after searching I finally found a tiny bit of cheese on the one half of the steak. Took a few bites and the meat had a lot of grizzle in it which I had to spit out   cause my jaw was having whip lash trying to chew it. So the wings were bad the cheese steak had vertually no cheese and had a lot of grizzle in the meat. This was our last trip to this place.

detailedReviews.text: Excellent customer service and great food

detailedReviews.author: Bobbie Weber
detailedReviews.text: Food and drinks were great, glad we picked this spot.

detailedReviews.author: Tim Walter
detailedReviews.text: Tonight I ordered a cheesesteak and fries. I asked for the fries to be fried hard. I got there to pick up my order and was told it would be about 2 minutes. No problem I said. Well that turned into 10 minutes and when my cheesesteak was done I saw my fries had been setting for that entire time. Of course when I got home 15 minutes later the fries were cold and mushy. If the cheesesteak had any cheese in it I sure didn't taste any or see any. Very disappointed. Will be a long time before and if I order food from there again.

The cheesesteak wasn‚Äôt horrible: seasoning was there, but not enough; a little too many fatty bits for my liking, as well. The fries got me heated though; unlike me, they were stone cold, dry, and flavorless. Unless they step up their game, definitely would not recommend.

detailedReviews.author: Jim Landrigan
detailedReviews.text: We came into the outside bar and we were enjoying our adult beverages. My wife picked up her panini which was very good. I had on a red hat that said Relax it‚Äôs just a red hat. Another group of 3 came in and one man had on a Trump shirt. I think it may have triggered Julie the bartender. She told us that we weren't allowed to talk politics which we weren‚Äôt in any heavy political discussion .  There is free speech in our country. I wanted you to know your bartenderJulie has cost you customers due to her belief that scolding your customers is her job.

detailedReviews.author: Susan Klacik
detailedReviews.text: We called them at 6:00 pm on a Saturday night to ask if they could accommodate our party of 20 because the arrangements we made (with a large retail outfit) fell through at the last minute. Without hesitation, they commenced to prepare a table and took excellent care of us throughout the evening. Thank GOD for wonderful places that still cater to large groups.

detailedReviews.author: Dennis Wink
detailedReviews.text: This is my second post as the first one looks deleted, anyway, I've been coming to this restaurant for a while and if I'm paying 20 dollars for a dinner I would expect descent size pieces of meat, my dinner had chicken and my friend had sausage with his pasta, the sausage was cut in paper thin half moons and the chicken was in small slivers like shredded cheese, you really had to move the pasta around to find the meat. The waitress got alittle snippy when she asked how everything was when I politely told her, she asked, other than that she was a good waitress and the food was still good. Now I know things are bad but if your paying 20 dollars for a dinner you expect more, maybe they were running low on chicken and sausage ü§î Can't wait for TOSCOS ITALIAN RESTAURANT to open, hope it's not much longer

detailedReviews.author: K L
detailedReviews.text: Some of the worst pizza around. I've had frozen pizza that was better that this. How do you consistently make a pizza with a soggy crust? Absolutely disgusting. Avoid the pizza at all costs!

detailedReviews.text: Seemed to have a lot of waitresses but because they weren't busy they disappeared for a long time so we ran out of drinks during and after the meal, and had to wait a while before we could ask for the check. Food was good.

detailedReviews.author: B. N.
detailedReviews.text: Like a good friend, this place is there. We find ourselves here after work or sports, without fail. Most of the food is excellent; even if it‚Äôs not, we‚Äôll always be there. Great service and prices. Love Paolo‚Äôs.

detailedReviews.text: Julie is the absolute rudest bartender I've ever met.

detailedReviews.author: jeremy chapa
detailedReviews.text:
Been along time since I was here. The food was good, the staff was friendly, the restaurant was clean.

I had bruschetta appetizer. Nicely done, only complaint toast points a little thick cut.

Then I had the lobster ravioli, with Ceasar salad, very good. Nice sauce.

The appetizer and main course came out way too fast, following each other immediately. I understand it's slow, but still watch ticket times.....

Got a bruschetta chicken sandwich to go, chicken was dry, sandwich looked like a train wreck.

All in all, I would return when I come back to Pennsylvania.

detailedReviews.author: Todd Cox
detailedReviews.text: I ordered a pickup 9/29 around 630pm, the order was wrong had to wait for correction. The Italian sub i ordered the roll was split apart completely, no oil and vinegar, super dry, the salad was brown and I ordered honey mustard dressing and never got that. Not sure if I'll go back, been ordering from there for years, this was by far the worst.
